lowers letting us know summer is opening her eyes\n\n- Debasish\n|\nPopularity does not happen overnight with a blink of an eye. It takes time, effort and creative knowledge to reach that particular goal in life.\n\n- Saaif\n|\nDevotion to goal, knowing your purpose and calling helps you go through pain, hindrance and crisis\n\n- Sunday\n|\nA row of trees far away, there on the hillside.But what is it, a row of trees? It’s just trees.Row and the plural trees aren’t things, they’re names.\n\n- Alberto Caeiro, The Keeper of Sheep\n|\nLeadership. Something you need few words for, acts are enough.\n\n- Alin\n|\nThis seems to be happening more and more, the dreams from the past blurring into reality and sadly, I preferred to be in the dream world rather than reality.\n\n- Emily  Williams, Letters to Eloise\n|\nWhen you develop yourself, you grow humanity.\n\n- Seema\n|\nFreedom of Speech doesn't justify online bullying. Words have power, be careful how you use them.\n\n- Germany\n|\nI don't think of all the misery, but of the beauty that still remains.\n\n- Anne Frank, The Diary of a Young Girl\n|\nAlone, alone. I am alone – I ache … Yet for the first time, despite all the anguish and the reality problems, I’m here. I feel tranquil, whole, ADULT.\n\n- Susan Sontag, As Consciousness is Harnessed to Flesh: Journals and Notebooks, 1964-1980\n|\nMany preach that do this way, do that way, have faith, speak the truth, have patience. These are all results (effects). How can results be changed?\n\n- Dada\n|\nOne writes to make a home for oneself, on paper, in time and in others' minds.\n\n- Alfred\n|\nNightmares have a dreadful effect of captivating our minds during the waking hours. Nevertheless, they are merely fiction.\n\n- Erin Forbes, Fire & Ice: The Elementals\n|\nIf you don't have a plan, you will never find enough time to finish a task.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nLearn to love someone when they least deserve it, because that is when they need your love most.\n\n- Rodolfo Costa, Advice My Parents Gave Me: and Other Lessons I Learned from My Mistakes\n|\nThe manlier you are, the harder it is to understand what a woman wants: there is not a hint of female brain in you.\n\n- Criss Jami, Killosophy\n|\nThe only noise now was the rain, pattering softly with the magnificent indifference of nature for the tangled passions of humans.\n\n- Sherwood\n|\nYour level of vibration runs parallel with your feelings, meaning you are in control of your life and the events that come into your life at any given moment.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Ask and the Universe Will Provide: A Straightforward Guide to Manifesting Your Dreams\n|\nTo fully encapsulate my creativity, I read to inhale, write to exhale. The whole process helps me breathe story.\n\n- Ace Antonio Hall, Lord of the Flies: Fitness for Writers\n|\nAnger dulls the sharpness of mind, hardens the softness of feelings, and replaces the sweetness of the world with bitterness.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nHappiness is largely about being socially connected, yet we cannot be connected if we keep on being so hard and unforgiving towards ourselves and on the scars we wear inside.\n\n- Jellis\n|\nTo put it simply, the lizard brain is purely concerned with survival.\n\n- Stephen\n|\nIf stars avoided the dark, they would not be visible at night.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nJust like a flower, you are a creation of unique beauty from the one essence of life.\n\n- Sharon Kirstin, The Answers Within\n|\nI count everything loss, to gain anything under the power of grace in Jesus Christ.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nDreams are hopeful because they exist as pure possibility. Unlike memories, which are fossils, long dead and buried deep.\n\n- Shaun David Hutchinson, We Are the Ants\n|\nNo struggle, no success. The stronger the thunder, the heavier the rainfall\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Become a Better You\n|\nNo answer I could provide to that question could possibly serve my own future interests.' Sarek straightened his sleeve and focused on her. 'More wine, Wife?\n\n- Keira Marcos, Tangled Destinies\n|\nAs she’d left, I’d glanced at her gun.This time, when she’d pointed it at me, she’d flicked the safety on. If that wasn’t true love, I don’t know what was.\n\n- Brandon Sanderson, Firefight\n|\nWith all eagerness, pursues your sacred dreams.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nTenderness of heart and kindness of the soul are not signs of weakness, but they are signs of inner strength.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI don't know much about gods, but I think the river is a strong, brown god\n\n- T.S.\n|\nProletarians of the world, look into the depths of your own beings, seek out the truth and realise it yourselves: you will find it nowhere else.\n\n- Peter Arshinov, History of the Makhnovist Movement, 1918-21\n|\nPractice is the hardest part of learning, and training is the essence of transformation.\n\n- Ann Voskamp, One Thousand Gifts: A Dare to Live Fully Right Where You Are\n|\nAmong the Kimbrii the greatest shame a person can bring to himself or his clan is to start a war, but the second greatest is to submit to tyranny or injustice without a fight.\n\n- Aleksandra Layland, Of Wisdom and Valor: The Art of War. The Path of Peace.\n|\nThis was after stew. But then, so is everything. When the first man crawled out of the slime and went to make his home on land, what he had for dinner that night was stew.\n\n- William Goldman, The Princess Bride\n|\nPeople do not deserve good writing, they are so pleased with bad.\n\n- Ralph\n|\nWhen you're the only sane person, you look like the only insane person.\n\n- Criss Jami, Diotima, Battery, Electric Personality\n|\nIf you have to ask if you’ve done enough, you haven’t. Each day brings with it the opportunity to do more than you did yesterday.\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Life, the Truth, and Being Free\n|\nI don't understand women at all. Like how a women can pour boiling hot wax onto their upper thigh, then rip the hair out by the root... and still be afraid of a spider.\n\n- Jerry\n|\nLove me like Saturday night, like three glasses of champagne, like the room is spinning, like you're drunk on my love.\n\n- C.J.\n|\nLife is like a river—it keeps flowing, flowing, and flowing till it merges into the sea. Nothing can stop the flow of Life, but you can enjoy the Journey.\n\n- RVM\n|\nStrange, what being forced to slow down could do to a person.\n\n- Nicholas Sparks, The Last Song\n|\nWhen the heart is torn and broken, only love and kindness can mend it.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWhen we are non-judgmental and mindful, we find peace in the moment and the moment becomes blissful.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nThere is no such things as magic, though there is such a thing as knowledge of the hidden ways of Nature.\n\n- H. Rider Haggard, She\n|\nHe looked at her as a man might look at a faded flower he had plucked, in which it was difficult for him to trace the beauty that had made him pick and so destroy it\n\n- Leo Tolstoy, Anna Karenina\n|\nLord, make me nowAs happy as the field.With flowers enriched...\n\n- Eileen\n|\nWhy do you write meaningless philosophy?” you asked. “Because it gives meaning to life,” I whispered with deep empathy.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nSomewhere along the way we all go a bit mad. So burn, let go and dive into the horror, because maybe it’s the chaos which helps us find where we belong.\n\n- Robert\n|\nCome to the woods, for here is rest, ...climb the mountains and get their good tidings. Nature's peace will flow into you as sunshine flows into trees.\n\n- John\n|\nAll who die, are all worldly beings (sansari – believing the worldly life to be real).\n\n- Dada\n|\nHe didn’t ask himself if she was beautiful, because the physical effect of her presence made the question insignificant.\n\n- Sebastian Faulks, Birdsong\n|\nStart with an honest analysis of why you are in opposition, not in government.\n\n- Philip Gould, The Unfinished Revolution: How New Labour Changed British Politics Forever\n|\nEvery morning, appreciate the golden glowing sun for giving you life. Every evening, appreciate yourself for making the world a little more joyful with your lovely presence.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nA person knows when they’re in darkness, even when they can’t see. -Nightblood\n\n- Brandon Sanderson, Warbreaker\n|\nWhen your heart, mind and soul is in harmony - you walk with love, you walk with beauty.\n\n- Angie\n|\nLife isn't static, and sometimes, we don't realize the value of knowledge or even of people, until further down the track, when we're mature enough to truly understand.\n\n- Nalini Singh, Archangel's Heart\n|\nMy life looked good on paper - where, in fact, almost all of it was being lived.\n\n- Martin Amis, Experience: A Memoir\n|\nWild roses are fairest, and nature a better gardener than art.\n\n- Louisa May Alcott, A Long Fatal Love Chase\n|\nWhen we look up at night and view the stars, everything we see is shinning because of distant nuclear fusion.\n\n- Carl Sagan, Cosmos\n|\nTo promote peace, promote understanding. To promote understanding, promote love.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nYou are safe with me.''I am not at all safe, with you. But I have no desire to be elsewhere.\n\n- A.S.\n|\nWe just need to hang in there a little longer, spend a little more of our energy... Breathe...\n\n- Melita Tessy, Battle of the Spheres: Crust, Mantle and Core\n|\nLet us be kind. Let us love to live in harmony, peace, and happiness.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nBeing a Christian doesn't mean trouble never comes our way, Zach. It just means God is here, and He gives us the grace to get through the heartache.\n\n- Colleen Coble, Tidewater Inn\n|\nWe do not need guns and bombs to bring peace, we need love and compassion.\n\n- Mother Teresa, The Joy in Loving: A Guide to Daily Living\n|\nWhen people went on vacation, they shed their home skins, thought they could be a new person.\n\n- Aimee Friedman, Sea Change\n|\nMind's acres are forever green: Oh, IShall keep perpetual summer here; I shallRefuse to let one startled swallow die,Or, from the copper beeches, one leaf fall.\n\n- Stanley\n|\nAgainst what is stupid, nonsensical, erroneous, and evil, [classical] liberalism fights with the weapons of the mind, and not with brute force and repression.\n\n- Ludwig von Mises, Liberalism\n|\nThe moon hung over the planet Earth, a dead thing over a dying thing.\n\n- John\n|\nIt was my journey and i had to do it without help. I had to find my own strengths, face my own fears.\n\n- Lois Lowry, Son\n|\nLife is not about who you know, but rather about who knows you & what you stand for. Show the world with presence, actions & the way you lead your life, who you are.\n\n- Akilnathan\n|\nOnly people who are capable of loving strongly can also suffer great sorrow, but this same necessity of loving serves to counteract their grief and heals them.\n\n- Leo\n|\nTo describe my mother would be to write about a hurricane in its perfect power. Or the climbing, falling colors of a rainbow.\n\n- Maya\n|\nNever give up, but learn to surrender as well\n\n- Zain\n|\nTo manifest the beauty of life, think beauty, dream beauty, and see the beauty in the simple things all around you.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIn the society of thinking humanity, the natural law of trust should be - In I, I trust.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, Principia Humanitas\n|\nPercy was getting tired of water.If he said that aloud, he would probably get kicked out of Poseidon’s Junior Sea Scouts, but he didn’t care.\n\n- Rick Riordan, The Mark of Athena\n|\nI believe that men are generally still a little afraid of the dark though the witches are all hung, and Christianity and candles have been introduced.\n\n- Anaïs\n|\nI want you here. I don't care if it's a hundred degrees and every blade of grass dies. Without you, none of that matters to me.\n\n- Kami\n|\nNever judge someone's character based on the words of another. Instead, study the motives behind the words of the person casting the bad judgment.\n\n- Suzy Kassem, Rise Up and Salute the Sun: The Writings of Suzy Kassem\n|